Cluster analysis [358] is a common unsupervised exploratory classification method. Events with similar patterns are included in the same homogeneous class/cluster. Because the patterns appear as points in the space of the features (the sensor outputs in the case of SAs), the clusters are spontaneously formed based on the distances between the events in this space. Generally, Euclidian metrics is employed to calculate the distances:2di,j=∑n=1qxi,n−xj,n212\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
