Univariate calibration relates one feature (sensor response) to one factor (target gas concentration). However, it does not involve only one event. To reduce the effect of experimental errors affecting both feature and factor, and to identify the type of relationship between them, a series of measurements (with replicates) is performed. In this way, one obtains a column vector of features x, containing the responses of the sensor to the corresponding concentrations of the analyte (also written as a column vector). In many cases, the relationship sought appears to be a linear regression x = s ∙ c + ex which, through simple matrix algebra, results in [323]:6s≅∑m=1Mcm·xm/∑m=1Mxm2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
